--> products.component.ts
selectProduct(item) {
    console.log(item);
    this.selectedProduct = item;
  }

a service is an interface to retrieve data
- localstorage
- API
- firewall

--> http.service.ts
1. import { HttpClient } from "@angular/common/http";
2. export class HttpService {
  constructor(public httpClient: HttpClient) {}
3. getProduct() {
    return this.httpClient.get("https://reqres.in/api/products");
  }
}

. one is current folder
.. two is next folder
array must has "s"

5 + 2 data type
1. string
2. number
3. boolean
4. array
5. object

-----> API
-->weather.component.ts, then go to http.service.ts
btnPressed() {
    this.httpService.getWeather(this.city).subscribe(  --> add "this.city"
      resp => {
        console.log(resp);
        this.weathers = resp["list"];
      }
    }

--> http.service.ts
getWeather(city) { --> add "city"
    return this.httpClient.get(
      "http://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/forecast/daily?q=" +
        city +
        "&cnt=10&appId=9fd7a449d055dba26a982a3220f32aa2"          --> change URL to +city+
    );
  }

1. http.service.ts -> getPlaces
2. dashboards.component.ts -> export "place" & ngOnInit
3. dashboards.component.html -> *ngFor="let place of places"

------->router
-->app-routing.module.ts, then go to app.component.html
import { ProductsComponent } from "./products/products.component";
import { AboutComponent } from "./about/about.component";
import { ContactComponent } from "./contact/contact.component";
import { ProductDetailComponent } from "./product-detail/product-detail.component";

const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: "products",
    component: ProductsComponent
  },
  {
    path: "about",
    component: AboutComponent
  },
  {
    path: "contact",
    component: ContactComponent
  },
  {
    path: "product-detail",
    component: ProductDetailComponent
  }
];

--> app.component.html
<ul>
    <li><a routerLink="/">Home</a></li>
    <li><a routerLink="/products">Product</a></li>
    <li><a routerLink="/about">About</a></li>
    <li><a routerLink="/contact">Contact</a></li>
  </ul>

--> install in terminal, then go to product.service.ts add import
ng g service product

--> after add product.service.ts, go to product.component.ts
import { ProductService } from "../product.service";
constructor(
    public productService: ProductService
  ) {}
ngOnInit() {
    this.items = this.productService.getProducts();
  }

--> back to product.service.ts
 getProductById(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < this.items.length; i++) {
      if (this.items[i]["id"] === id) {
        return this.items[i];
      }
    }
    return null;
  }

--> go to product-detail.component(active the route)
import { ActivatedRoute } from "@angular/router";
import { ProductService } from "./product.service";
constructor(
    public route: ActivatedRoute,
    public productService: ProductService
  ) {}
ngOnInit() {
    this.route.params.subscribe(params => {
      console.log(params["id"]);
      this.selectedProduct.getProductById(params["id"]);
    });
  }


